cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically the problem of estimating the layout of a complex urban driving scenario from a single image. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep neural networks and adversarial feature learning, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem of estimating the layout of a driving scenario also involves robotics and autonomous vehicles, which falls under the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves semantic occupancy grids and semantic segmentation, which are common in the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
